# Git Pull — Generic (Any Project)

## **Overview**

Use this rule when the user asks to **`git pull`** one or more repositories — **pull only** (no commit, no push, no release deploy).

**Related rules (do not use for pull-only requests):**
- [git_local_push.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_local_push.mdc) — commit, push, secret filter, release merge
- [git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc) — multi-repo commit/push batch
- [deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc) — GH_TOKEN auth on this machine

**Copy-paste user prompt:**

```
git pull this project "F:\project_workspace\<repo-name>"
Follow .cursor/rules/git_pull.mdc
```

For multiple repos, list each path on its own line.

---

## **Scope**

- **DO** run `git fetch` + `git pull` on the **current branch** (`git branch --show-current`).
- **DO** verify `git status -sb` and report whether pull was already up to date, fast-forward, or merge.
- **DO** attempt conflict resolution before reporting a blocker.
- **DO** preserve local uncommitted changes when pull succeeds without conflict (they remain dirty after fast-forward).
- **DON'T** commit, push, or merge to `release/v1.0.0` unless the user explicitly asks.
- **DON'T** change `git config` (no global credential or SSL config edits).

---

## **Pre-checks (Windows / this machine)**

```powershell
$env:GH_TOKEN = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable('GH_TOKEN', 'User')
gh auth setup-git
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
```

- **DO NOT** run interactive `gh auth login` while User-level `GH_TOKEN` is valid.
- Pull over HTTPS may need `GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY` for this machine (session only — do not persist).

---

## **Standard pull workflow (single repo)**

```powershell
cd F:\project_workspace\<repo-name>
$branch = git branch --show-current
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'

git fetch origin
git status -sb
git log HEAD..origin/$branch --oneline

git pull origin $branch

git diff --name-only --diff-filter=U
git status -sb
git status --porcelain

Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

| `git pull` result | Action |
|-------------------|--------|
| **Already up to date** | Report synced; list any local dirty paths |
| **Fast-forward** | Remote applied — report new HEAD SHA and subject |
| **Merge commit created** | Pull succeeded — report merge commit |
| **CONFLICT** | Resolve (below) or report **BLOCKER** |
| **error: Your local changes would be overwritten** | Stash → pull → stash pop (below) |

---

## **Multi-repo batch pull**

When the user lists multiple paths, run the **standard workflow** for **each repo independently**. One repo failing does not stop others.

```powershell
$repos = @(
  'F:\project_workspace\mosc-temp',
  'F:\project_workspace\event-site-manager-service'
)
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
foreach ($repo in $repos) {
  Push-Location $repo
  $branch = git branch --show-current
  git fetch origin
  git pull origin $branch
  Pop-Location
}
Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

Report a **COMPLETED** row per repo (branch, before/after SHA, pull type) and **BLOCKERS** for any failure.

